    {
      "id": "ecb97b72e69ad95f33e6b421a7fd7c364c3e3fc0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-08-08 18:33:30.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nTwo notes on this patch:\n- in LFSCK phase 2 it is starting to flag the OST objects separately on disk in the LMA so that it can tell if this is a named (MDT object in OI) or unnamed (OST in O/{seq}) object during recovery. It flags this in the object in memory and it makes sense to use the same flag here.\n- the use of the FLDB in the OSD is only to distinguish between the OST and MDT objects and IMHO should be removed entirely. Each OST knows which sequences belong to it already because it can check O/* for the list of sequences, and the OSD shouldn't need a network connection to work properly. This patch is a step in the right direction, but if like to see this finished off.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "53695da85cebf4739ed55d662ed0d7f1df1f6505",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-08-08 18:41:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(4 inline comments)\n\n> the use of the FLDB in the OSD is only to distinguish between the OST and MDT objects and IMHO should be removed entirely. Each OST knows which sequences belong to it already because it can check O/* for the list of sequences, and the OSD shouldn't need a network connection to work properly. This patch is a step in the right direction, but if like to see this finished off.\n\nAFAIU, FLDB is also used learn whether specific FID is local. I'd hope that OSD can maintain a local list of sequences it manages (should be easy to maintain at object create?).\n\nI agree that it's better do not use FLDB here.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "172a71c96ffd9c2feb5eb6adc345ff76406ee4ea",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-08-08 18:50:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n(2 inline comments)\n\nI think this patch is ok for a quick fix for master to get it moving forward for DAT testing. \n\nI'd like to pursue some mechanism to get a simple OSD-internal FLDB to meet its needs. The \"O\" directory is almost the same as the local FLDB, but only for OST objects. Need some simple mechanism to easily know if a given sequence is in the OI.\n\nSince UT and LFSCK phase 2 will not make it into 2.5 we have done time to fix this properly.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "b6d05c2c30d09892fc03493a88ec29aaef405748",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-08-08 18:52:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nHmm, are we overlooking the obvious?  Doesn't each OST and MDT get assigned a super-sequence from the controller? If this seq range could be told to the OSD then it would be easy to know all of the valid local sequences for the OSD.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "5f2d7545e505e32910eda0e9ac08953596ecf286",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-08-08 18:54:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nsome cleanups after the landing still needed, IMHO. like that CERROR(). and I'd rather not introduce a dependency on the service name, if possible. it's better to start checking /O and later add support for MDT objects.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "fbc00fbc21db4780dcabb4381e684ce49bda087d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
